%N A395847 Decimal expansion of the expected distance between the center of a unit-side regular pentagon to a randomly and uniformly selected point on its perimeter.
%H A395847 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395847 Equals (sqrt(10*(5 + sqrt(5))) + (5 + 2*sqrt(5))*arccosh(sqrt(5) - 1))/20.
%F A395847 Equals (5+2*sqrt(5))*(tan(Pi/5)*sec(Pi/5) + arcsinh(tan(Pi/5)))/20.
%F A395847 Equals (sqrt(5)*phi^3/20)*(2*tan(Pi/5)/phi + log(2/phi + tan(Pi/5))), where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%e A395847 0.744666853936194163107459534588181561974365758435389...
%t A395847 RealDigits[(Sqrt[10*(5 + Sqrt[5])] + (5 + 2*Sqrt[5])*ArcCosh[Sqrt[5] - 1])/20, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395847 (PARI) (sqrt(10*(5 + sqrt(5))) + (5 + 2*sqrt(5))*acosh(sqrt(5) - 1))/20
%Y A395847 Cf. A001622, A394596, A395846 (equilateral triangle), A345653 (square), A395848 (regular hexagon).
